📱 What is App Development?

At its core, App Development is the process of designing, building, testing, and maintaining software applications that run on devices like smartphones, tablets, computers, and even smart TVs.
These applications — commonly called “apps” — are created to perform specific tasks such as messaging, gaming, shopping, learning, or managing finances.

App Development involves multiple layers — from writing code and creating user interfaces to connecting databases and ensuring smooth performance. Developers use programming languages like Java, Swift, Kotlin, Python, and JavaScript to bring app ideas to life.

⸻

🏠 Analogy

Imagine you’re building a house:
	•	The architect designs the layout (UI/UX Design).
	•	The engineers construct the building (Coding).
	•	The plumbers and electricians add essential connections (APIs and Databases).
	•	Finally, you decorate and test everything before moving in (Testing & Deployment).

App Development follows a similar pattern — you plan, build, test, and release the final product so users can interact with it seamlessly.

