⏳ When did App Development Start?

The journey of app development evolved alongside the rise of digital devices:
	•	1990s – Early Days:
Apps started with desktop software — simple utilities and games for personal computers.
	•	2007 – Mobile Revolution:
The launch of the iPhone and later Android introduced the concept of mobile apps through the App Store and Google Play.
	•	2010s – Cloud & Cross-Platform Era:
Apps began to integrate with cloud storage and support multiple platforms (like React Native, Flutter).
	•	2020s – AI & AR Integration:
Modern apps now use AI, AR/VR, and machine learning for smarter, personalized experiences — like chatbots, face filters, and smart assistants.

